rComments: Glover sounds  monotone and as if he's talking to himself because he doesn't engage with his students such as asking what we think of a topic. You MUST read the chapters before going to lecture for it to make sense, it'll be all gibberish if you don't. He's smart and can explain the topic well but you need to work on trying not to fall asleep.

Prof. Glover is super down to earth and approachable. In fact, probably the nicest professor I've had at UTSC. The course material is challenging, but that's expected. He's clear and concise about what is covered on the exam though. Awesome guy! Would take another chem course at UTSC if he taught others.

He is sometimes unclear/hard to follow in lecture. But he is enthusiastic and seems really passionate about teaching. He seems to genuinely care about students/the learning experience. This is a rarity.
challenging material but makes biology amazing
a smart guy but just can't teach.
